        {
          "front": "My name is",
          "back": "اسمي",
          "romanized": "ismi",
          "grammarNote": "اسمي (ismi) = my name is (lit. 'my name'). اسم (ism) = name + ي (i) = my. Arabic possessives are suffixes on the noun: اسمك (your name), اسمه (his name), اسمها (her name). No verb needed — just say اسمي + the name."
